+# Lock System Sharding Backport Documentation
+
+This document records the backport of MySQL 8.0 WL#10314 (Lock-sys optimization: sharded lock_sys mutex) to Percona Server 5.7.
+
+## Overview
+
+The goal is to reduce lock contention on `lock_sys->mutex` by implementing a sharded locking scheme similar to MySQL 8.0. The single global mutex is replaced with:
+
+1. A sharded read-write lock (`global_latch`) for coarse-grained synchronization
+2. 512 page shards for record lock protection
+3. 512 table shards for table lock protection
+
