+- Added `lock_sys_global_rw_lock` to `all_innodb_rwlocks[]` array
+
+## C++03 Adaptations
+
+The following C++11/14 features from MySQL 8.0 were adapted for C++03 compatibility:
+
+| MySQL 8.0 Feature | MySQL 5.7 Adaptation |
+|-------------------|----------------------|
+| `constexpr` | `static const` |
+| `thread_local` | `UNIV_THREAD_LOCAL` (maps to `__thread` on Linux) |
+| `= delete` | Private declaration without implementation |
+| `= default` | Explicit implementation |
+| `auto` | Explicit type declarations |
+| `using T::T` | No inheriting constructors |
+| Delegating constructors | Not available, use explicit initialization |
+| `noexcept` | Removed |
+| `std::less<>{}` | Address comparison via helper functions |
+| List initialization `{}` | Constructor calls `()` |
+| `ut::Location{__FILE__, __LINE__}` | `ut::Location(__FILE__, __LINE__)` via explicit constructor |
+
+## RAII Guard Classes
+
+The following guard classes are provided for convenient latch management:
+
+| Class | Usage |
+|-------|-------|
+| `Global_exclusive_latch_guard` | Exclusive lock on global latch (for "stop the world" operations) |
+| `Global_exclusive_try_latch` | Non-blocking try-lock on global latch |
+| `Global_shared_latch_guard` | Shared lock on global latch |
+| `Shard_naked_latch_guard` | Lock on specific shard (requires global s-latch held) |
+| `Shard_latch_guard` | Combined global s-latch + shard latch |
+| `Shard_naked_latches_guard` | Lock on two shards (for lock movement) |
+| `Shard_latches_guard` | Combined global s-latch + two shard latches |
+| `Unsafe_global_latch_manipulator` | Static methods for temporary release/reacquire of global x-latch |
+
+## Usage Examples
+
+Guard classes are used directly with `UT_LOCATION_HERE` macro for source location tracking:
+
+```cpp
+/* Global exclusive latch guard */
+locksys::Global_exclusive_latch_guard guard(UT_LOCATION_HERE);
+
+/* Table shard latch guard */
+locksys::Shard_latch_guard shard_guard(UT_LOCATION_HERE, table);
+
+/* Page shard latch guard */
+locksys::Shard_latch_guard page_guard(UT_LOCATION_HERE, page_id);
+
+/* Two-block shard latches guard */
+locksys::Shard_latches_guard latches_guard(UT_LOCATION_HERE, block_a, block_b);
+
+/* Unsafe global latch manipulation */
+locksys::Unsafe_global_latch_manipulator::exclusive_unlatch();
+locksys::Unsafe_global_latch_manipulator::exclusive_latch(UT_LOCATION_HERE);
+```
+
+## Helper Functions
+
+The following inline helper functions are provided in `lock0guards.cc` for consistent mutex ordering:
+
+```cpp
+get_mutex_with_smaller_addr(mutex_a, mutex_b)  // Returns mutex with smaller address
+get_mutex_with_larger_addr(mutex_a, mutex_b)   // Returns mutex with larger address
+```
+
+These are used by `Shard_naked_latches_guard` to acquire multiple mutexes in address order, preventing deadlocks.
+
