+## Locks_hashtable
+
+The `Locks_hashtable` class provides a hash table for storing record locks, with the following features:
+
+### Methods
+
+| Method | Description |
+|--------|-------------|
+| `append(lock, hash_value)` | Appends a lock to the end of its hash chain |
+| `prepend(lock, hash_value)` | Prepends a lock to the beginning of its hash chain |
+| `erase(lock, hash_value)` | Removes a lock from its hash chain |
+| `move_to_front(lock, hash_value)` | Moves a lock to the front of its hash chain |
+| `resize(n_cells)` | Resizes the hash table to a new number of cells |
+| `get_n_cells()` | Returns the number of cells |
+| `get_cell_id(hash_value)` | Returns the cell ID for a given hash value |
+| `find_set_in_this_shard(start_pos)` | Finds the next non-empty cell in the same shard |
+| `get_first(cell_id)` | Returns the first lock in a cell |
+
+### Sharded Bitset
+
+The `Cells_in_use` bitset tracks which hash table cells contain locks, enabling efficient iteration:
+- Uses `Sharded_bitset<512>` with 512 shards matching the latch shards
+- `find_set_in_this_shard()` allows iterating only over non-empty cells within a shard
+- Avoids scanning empty cells during lock iteration
+
